.TH "i2c_transfer_buffer_flags" 9 "i2c_transfer_buffer_flags" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i2c_transfer_buffer_flags \- issue a single I2C message transferring data to/from a buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i2c_transfer_buffer_flags
.BI "(const struct i2c_client *client "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "int count "  ","
.BI "u16 flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "client" 12
Handle to slave device
.IP "buf" 12
Where the data is stored
.IP "count" 12
How many bytes to transfer, must be less than 64k since msg.len is u16
.IP "flags" 12
The flags to be used for the message, e.g. I2C_M_RD for reads
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns negative errno, or else the number of bytes transferred.
